title: Blinken Defends Bypassing Congress to Sell Weapons to Israel and Urges Lawmakers to Help Ukraine
description: Secretary of State Antony Blinken on Sunday defended the emergency sale to Israel of nearly 14,000 rounds of tank ammunition.

title: Fighting Rages On Across Gaza as Israel Moves Ahead With Renewed U.S. Support
description: Heavy fighting raged Sunday across Gaza as Israel pressed ahead with its offensive after the U.S. blocked the latest push for a ceasefire.

title: Tennessee Tornadoes Kill at Least Six. Here’s What to Know
description: Severe storms and tornadoes that swept across Tennessee killed six people and injured at least two dozen more on Saturday.

title: Why Mars Boss Poul Weihrauch Wants to Help Other CEOs on Climate Goals
description: Weihrauch spoke with TIME about how he is thinking about impact, working with the Mars family and why the company is opening up.
